Francis Aura a student at Kivaywa Secondary School in Kakamega County is on the verge of dropping out of school, as a result of lack of fees. The talented student has been selling sesame seeds, popularly known locally as simsim and making mats in Lumakanda Lugari constituency. His quest to benefit from the constituency development fund has hit a dead end. He amazed the KTN News team when he traveled all the way to Nairobi to deliver a customised KTN News mat.